<HL>
   Business Brief -- PacifiCorp:
   Pacific Telecom Unit Bids
   For Mid-Plains Telephone
</HL>
<DATE>
12/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 10
</SO>
<CO>
   PPW PTCM
</CO>
<IN>
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Pacific Telecom Inc., a unit of PacifiCorp, a Portland,
Ore.-based utility holding company, said it proposed to
acquire Mid-Plains Telephone Inc. by exchanging PacifiCorp
common stock valued at about $51 million for all of the
common shares of the Middleton, Wis., company.
   Mid-Plains provides local phone service in Middleton,
Cross Plains and parts of Madison. It had total assets of
$27.3 million on Sept. 30, Pacific Telecom said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Under the bid, made to the Mid-Plains board, Mid-Plains
holders would receive for each share about 1.19 PacifiCorp
common shares. Pacific Telecom said MidPlains has 1,933,467
shares outstanding. PacifiCorp shares closed Friday at
$22.375, up 37.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite
trading. Mid-Plains officials couldn't be reached for
comment.
   "This offer is consistent with our commitment to expand
our business . . . in the rural and suburban areas of
Wisconsin," C.E. Robinson, Pacific Telecom chairman and chief
executive officer, said.
</TEXT>
