<LP>
   PUBLISHING: Encyclopaedia Britannica Inc. agreed to
publish a Russian-language edition with Progress Publishers
of the Soviet Union. The first 12 volumes of the New
Encyclopaedia Britannica will be translated into Russian and
combined with "local editorial material" for the Soviet
Union. It is expected to take five years.
</LP>
